-- Real estate company Store Capital files for IPO
-- 
-- Fri Aug 29, 2014 03:55PM EDT
-- None



Aug 29 (Reuters) - Real estate company Store Capital Corp filed with U.S. regulators on Friday to raise up to $500 million in an initial public offering of common stock.

The Scottsdale, Arizona-based company listed Goldman Sachs, Credit Suisse and Morgan Stanley among the underwriters to the IPO. (http://1.usa.gov/1lAi0za)